    <h3>Paper</h3>
    <p>
        - Paper can be recycled by pulping it and then re-forming sheets of paper from the pulp.<br>
        - Recycling paper saves trees, energy, water, and landfill space.<br>
        - Paper can only be recycled a limited number of times because the fibres get shorter and weaker as they are cut.
    </p>
    <br>
    <h3>Plastics</h3>
    <p>
        - Some plastics can be recycled by melting and remoulding them to make new products.<br>
        - Different types of plastic have to be separated before recycling.<br>
        - Some plastics can be recycled chemically by breaking them down into their monomers which can then be used to make new polymers.<br>
        - Not all plastics can be recycled - some are thermosetting plastics which cannot be melted and remoulded.
    </p>
